---
layout: base.njk
metaTitle: "Designers adapting to AI — field notes from a designer turned product manager"
description: "How designers can adapt to AI: honest field notes, adaptation strategies and career lessons from a career designer turned product manager."
---

{# HERO #}
<header class="hero">
  <div class="mono eyebrow fade-1">// designer by trade · product manager by adaptation</div>
  <h1 class="display hero-h1 fade-2">AI learned<br>to <span class="strike">draw.</span></h1>
  <div class="hero-hand fade-3">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 90 60" width="70" aria-hidden="true" class="draw-in hero-arrow">
      <path d="M6 8 C 30 30, 45 42, 74 46 M74 46 l-14 -8 M74 46 l-6 -14" fill="none" stroke="var(--blue)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" pathLength="1"/>
    </svg>
    <span class="hand hero-scrawl">so what happens to <em>us</em>?</span>
  </div>
  <p class="hero-sub fade-4">
    theDoodleGuy is field notes on adapting to the AI wave — from a career designer who's already
    made one big pivot, into product management. The tools worth your time, the skills that keep
    their value, and honest lessons from the move.
  </p>
  <div class="hero-ctas fade-4">
    <a class="btn btn-blue" href="/blog/">Read the blog</a>
    <a class="btn btn-outline" href="#newsletter">Get the newsletter</a>
  </div>
</header>

{# PROBLEM #}
<section class="problem">
  <div class="section-head">
    <div class="mono eyebrow">// the problem</div>
    <h2 class="display">The ground is moving.<br><span class="hl">Standing still is a choice.</span></h2>
  </div>
  <div class="cards">
    <div class="card tilt-l">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" width="52" aria-hidden="true" class="card-doodle">
        <g fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <rect x="14" y="20" width="36" height="30" rx="6" transform="rotate(-2 32 35)"/>
          <circle cx="25" cy="33" r="2.6" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"/>
          <circle cx="40" cy="32" r="2.6" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"/>
          <path d="M25 42 q 7 5 14 -1"/><path d="M32 20 v-7 m0 0 a3 3 0 1 1 .1 0"/>
        </g>
      </svg>
      <h3>The tools ship weekly</h3>
      <p>Image models, layout generators, code-from-a-sketch. Every month something new claims a
         slice of what used to be billable hours.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card tilt-r">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" width="52" aria-hidden="true" class="card-doodle">
        <g fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <rect x="8" y="18" width="48" height="28" rx="4" transform="rotate(1.5 32 32)"/>
          <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="8"/>
          <path d="M32 27 v10 M29 29.5 q 3 -2 6 0 M29 34.5 q 3 2 6 0"/>
        </g>
      </svg>
      <h3>Clients did the math</h3>
      <p>"Can't AI do this cheaper?" is now a normal email. If you can't articulate your value
         beyond the artefact, the market will answer for you.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card tilt-l">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" width="52" aria-hidden="true" class="card-doodle">
        <g fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.6" stroke-linecap="round">
          <path d="M32 8 a24 24 0 1 1 -1 0 M32 8 a24 25 0 1 1 -2 .3"/>
          <path d="M32 18 v15 l11 6"/><path d="M52 6 l6 6 M12 6 l-6 6"/>
        </g>
      </svg>
      <h3>Skills expire faster</h3>
      <p>The half-life of a technical skill keeps shrinking. What compounds now isn't tool mastery
         — it's taste, judgement, and the ability to adapt on purpose.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="hand problem-note">(none of this means designers are finished. it means the job description changed.)</p>
</section>

{# STORY #}
<section class="story">
  <div class="story-inner">
    <div class="story-sketch" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 240 200" width="100%">
  <g fill="none" stroke="var(--ink)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
    <!-- human -->
    <circle cx="60" cy="52" r="22"/>
    <path d="M50 48 q3 -4 7 0 M63 48 q3 -4 7 0"/>
    <path d="M52 61 q8 7 17 -1"/>
    <path d="M60 74 v56 M60 88 l-22 22 M60 88 l35 14"/>
    <path d="M60 130 l-15 35 M60 130 l15 35"/>
  </g>
  <g fill="none" stroke="var(--blue)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
    <!-- robot -->
    <rect x="150" y="30" width="44" height="36" rx="6" transform="rotate(2 172 48)"/>
    <path d="M172 30 v-10 m0 0 a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 .1 0"/>
    <circle cx="163" cy="46" r="2.6" fill="var(--blue)" stroke="none"/>
    <circle cx="181" cy="46" r="2.6" fill="var(--blue)" stroke="none"/>
    <path d="M164 56 q8 5 16 0"/>
    <rect x="152" y="72" width="40" height="46" rx="6" transform="rotate(-1.5 172 95)"/>
    <path d="M152 84 l-30 14 -20 4"/>
    <path d="M162 118 v30 m20 -30 v30"/>
    <path d="M158 148 h10 m14 0 h10"/>
  </g>
  <!-- handshake sparks -->
  <g stroke="var(--yellow)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round">
    <path d="M97 88 l4 -8 M106 90 l7 -5 M108 100 l9 1"/>
  </g>
  <text x="120" y="188" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Caveat, cursive" font-size="15" fill="var(--red)">me, shaking hands with the robot</text>
</svg>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="mono eyebrow">// why listen to this guy</div>
      <h2 class="display">This isn't my first plot twist.</h2>
      <p>I spent my career as a designer, and I was in the room when the "this will replace you"
         tool arrived — more than once. My own adaptation was moving up the stack: I now work as a
         product manager, where I see daily how AI is reshaping what teams expect from design.</p>
      <p>That vantage point — a designer's hands, a product manager's seat at the table — is what
         this site runs on. Real stories, tested workflows, and straight answers about which
         skills to build next, so you adapt on your terms, not the algorithm's.</p>
      <a class="btn btn-ink" href="/blog/this-isnt-my-first-extinction-event/">Read: "This isn't my first extinction event"</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# LATEST POSTS #}
<section class="blog-preview">
  <div class="section-head row">
    <div>
      <div class="mono eyebrow">// fresh from the sketchbook</div>
      <h2 class="display">Latest field notes</h2>
    </div>
    <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/blog/">All posts →</a>
  </div>
  <div class="post-grid">
    {% for post in collections.posts %}
      {% if loop.index <= 3 %}
      <article class="post-card">
        <div class="post-meta mono">
          <span class="tag tag-{{ post.data.pillar | replace(' ', '') | lower }}">{{ post.data.pillar }}</span>
          <span>{{ post.date | readableDate }} · {{ post.data.readTime }}</span>
        </div>
        <h3><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a></h3>
        <p>{{ post.data.excerpt }}</p>
        <a class="hand read-more" href="{{ post.url }}">read it →</a>
      </article>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

{% include "newsletter.njk" %}
